I did rough calculation of the total burn time for the Merlin engines on this booster:
The nine engines have gone through 5 full-length test burns before each launch, 4 re-entry burns, and 4 landing burns: 9*18=162 engine-starts.
They have been through a total of 5 * 145 s boost burn + 4 * 20 s re-entry burn + 4* 40 s landing burn = 965 seconds (about 16 minutes) per engine (9*16=144 minutes total) before one of them fails! That's pretty good going in my book :-)
Question for Mr. Dodd: Do you know of any other single rocket engine which have been fired for more than 16 minutes total?
